		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Perhaps being more specific would help. It could be a number of things. You should look and see if any I/O lines are broken, or maybe your cart connector/game is dirty. If any I/O lines are broken, that's probably the answer. Many other broken parts would cause this problem. Obviously, one of the above is most likely the cause of this...
<br />
<br />Also, this should've probably been in the hardware section of the forum, but that's okay. Just post about this kind of stuff there next time.

		

