	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Tue Feb 21, 2006 9:50 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: a question</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">lord_Chile wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">If you disable rendering (lda #0 sta $2001) ....<br /><br />tokumaru says me that by disabling rendering you can making a special effect like flickering, but i didnt get it fully..</div>
<br />Hey, that is not what I said... O.o
<br />"lda #0 sta $2001" will disable all rendering and will not produce any flickering effect. You could do it like this if you wanted a "flashing" effect, like a thunder or something. You'd disable rendering and have $2006 point to a bright color in the palette every other frame to have the screen "flash" between your regular game screen and white, for example.
<br />
<br />The thing with sprites is different. You alternate between rendering and not rendering <strong>only a group of sprites</strong> (the ones that make up the player), not the whole screen! For this there is no "disable rendering of main character" flag, you'll have to manually place the character's sprites off-screen, so it looks like it's not there. Do that alternatingly and the sprite will flicker.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


